    "updated_at": "2026-04-16T15:28:29Z",
    "body": "This is the same issue as #6255 - and fixed by the PR for that issue.\n\nAs a workaround until it's merged+released, you can take [the file](https://github.com/bozenalabs/starship/blob/6b63c6f403c72b8a0b0ffeb16975f766a00723f3/src/init/starship.zsh) that PR changes and source it instead of where you're currently doing `eval \"$(starship init zsh)\"`\n\nIt's hard to believe that issue has been sitting in the zsh init for 5 years...  Also, the bash init has a similar variable assignment, I'm a little surprised it works too.",
