    "created_at": "2026-04-20T16:24:55Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-04-20T16:24:55Z",
    "body": "> This is the same issue as [#6255](https://github.com/starship/starship/issues/6255) - and fixed by the PR for that issue.\n> \n> As a workaround until it's merged+released, you can take [the file](https://github.com/bozenalabs/starship/blob/6b63c6f403c72b8a0b0ffeb16975f766a00723f3/src/init/starship.zsh) that PR changes and source it instead of where you're currently doing `eval \"$(starship init zsh)\"`\n> \n> It's hard to believe that issue has been sitting in the zsh init for 5 years... Also, the bash init has a similar variable assignment, I'm a little surprised it works too.\n\nThank you for suggesting the workaround, but it doesn't quite work for me out of the box. The file `starship.zsh` contains placeholder strings `::STARSHIP::` which somehow get replaced with the pathname of the starship binary when `eval \"(starship init zsh)\"` is used.",
